page_title: 'Quickstart: Generate images with the Python SDK for Azure OpenAI Service'
page_description: Learn how to generate images with Azure OpenAI Service by using the Python SDK and the endpoint and access keys for your Azure OpenAI resource.
chunk_content: Install the Python SDKOpen a command prompt and browse to your project folder. Install the OpenAI Python SDK by using the following command:#### DALL-E 3```bashpip install openai```#### DALL-E 2 (preview)> [!IMPORTANT]> The latest release of the OpenAI Python library does not currently support DALL-E 2 when used with Azure OpenAI. To access DALL-E 2 with Azure OpenAI use version `0.28.1`. Or, follow the migration guide to use DALL-E 2 with OpenAI 1.x.```bashpip install openai==0.28.1```---Install the following libraries as well:```bashpip install requestspip install pillow ```
